19:58.620 --> 20:01.286
<i>'Cause it doesn't matter
how big the storm</i>

20:01.321 --> 20:03.488
<i>or how much stuff
gets blown your way--</i>

20:03.690 --> 20:06.301
<i>If you have each other,
that's everything.</i>

20:06.530 --> 20:08.420
<i>'Cause there's nothing
more important than--</i>

20:08.580 --> 20:10.920
<i>Holy crap!
Is that a dryer?</i>

20:13.470 --> 20:15.570
You see it, too,
right, Mike?

20:16.240 --> 20:18.188
The tornado
gave us a dryer.

20:20.230 --> 20:22.078
Quick. Get it inside
before anybody sees.

20:24.360 --> 20:26.330
Oh, my. Whoo!

20:27.650 --> 20:30.140
<i>Our luck started to
turn around after that.</i>

20:30.290 --> 20:32.347
<i>Some stupid bank
actually approved us</i>

20:32.382 --> 20:33.800
<i>for a brand-new
credit card,</i>

20:33.970 --> 20:36.211
<i>so we paid off
Brick's library fines...</i>

20:36.950 --> 20:39.020
<i>We were able
to afford contacts for Sue,</i>

20:39.140 --> 20:40.716
<i>and she actually made
the swim team--</i>

20:40.820 --> 20:42.944
<i>Well, 34th alternate.</i>

20:43.350 --> 20:45.210
<i>And the best part of
the new credit card?</i>

20:45.330 --> 20:47.237
<i>No payments till 2012.</i>

20:47.460 --> 20:49.270
<i>And I'm sure by 2012,</i>

20:49.440 --> 20:51.120
<i>everything's gonna be great.</i>

20:51.270 --> 20:54.770
Okay. See, this is why
you never give up hope--

20:54.910 --> 20:56.600
because
anything is possible.

20:56.740 --> 20:58.750
I mean, you just never know
what's gonna happen.

20:58.880 --> 21:01.499
You just gotta hang in
there and believe and--

21:01.680 --> 21:03.960
Hot damn!
There's even clothes in there!

